## <a id="1-1-0"></a> v1.1.0

**Release Date: February 05, 2021**

**1.1.0** represents the second minor release of Tanzu Build Service.

This release includes the 0.2.0 release of kpack

* Image signing with Notary V1
* Includes [Lifecycle 0.10.2](https://github.com/buildpacks/lifecycle/releases/tag/v0.10.2)
* Support for CustomStacks (based on Ubuntu bionic)
* Add Windows support (**Beta**)
* Improved logging for Image builds
    * Display Build reason and change diff
    * Log fetching source
    * More descriptive errors
* Allow source images to contain zip, tar, and tar.gz files
* Dedupe build secrets (if service account has repeats)
* Improved validation when Image cache size is specified

This release includes the 0.2.0 release of kpack-cli

* Filter option for Image list
* Display builds across images for Build list
* New command to update Lifecycle
* Option to view Bill of Materials for Build status
* Remove Buildpackage from ClusterStore using Buildpackage Id and version
* Import exits with an error if the resulting builders are not ready
* Print status message when ClusterStores or ClusterStacks are not ready
* Display version in detection order of ClusterBuilder and Builder status
* Display Build reason and changes for Build status
* Handle registry secrets created with repo path
* Fix registry issue when running on Windows
* Fix for Stack upload failing on a Windows machine

### Product Snapshot

Tanzu Build Service 1.0.4 ships with the following components:

* [kpack 0.2.0](https://github.com/pivotal/kpack/releases/tag/v0.2.0)
* [kpack cli v0.2.0](https://github.com/vmware-tanzu/kpack-cli/releases/tag/v0.2.0)
* [CNB lifecycle v0.10.2](https://github.com/buildpacks/lifecycle/releases/tag/v0.10.2)
* [Stacks Operator v0.0.3]

Tanzu Build Service supports and utilizes [Tanzu Buildpacks](https://docs.pivotal.io/tanzu-buildpacks).

### Product Dependencies

Build Service can be installed on any Kubernetes cluster (v1.16 or later).

### Upgrade Path

v1.0.* can be upgraded to v1.1.0. Please follow the [install](installing.html) process to upgrade.


